Leading independent data, voice, and IP provider, Liquid Telecom presented its productivity and platform-based tools at the 2018 MyBroadband Cloud, Hosting, and Security Conference, which took place at the Gallagher Convention Centre in Midrand on 13 June. “Our tools enable businesses to undertake digital transformation journeys,” said Reshaad Sha, Liquid Telecom CEO. “On the productivity side, these are underpinned by Microsoft’s Office 365, Teams, Unified Communications, and Disaster Recovery, while the connectivity side includes Cloud Connect.” The MyBroadband Cloud Conference provides IT executives, managers, and business owners from various industries with a platform to interact and do business with South Africa’s top cloud and hosting providers. For more information, watch the video below of Liquid Telecom at the conference.  This article was published in partnership with Liquid Telecom.